    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a full kettle</p><p>Peel and finely dice your <strong>shallot[s]</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-nduja-risotto-with-zesty-tenderstem-broccoli/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced shallot </strong>and <strong>chopped garlic</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until softened</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-nduja-risotto-with-zesty-tenderstem-broccoli/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the shallot is softening, chop your <strong>cherry tomatoes</strong> in half</p><p>Once softened, add the <strong>halved tomatoes</strong> to the pan and cook for 3-4 min or until the tomatoes are beginning to soften</p><p>Meanwhile, dissolve your<strong> chicken stock mix</strong> in 750ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[975ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[1.4L]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>\u2013 this is your<strong> chicken stock</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-nduja-risotto-with-zesty-tenderstem-broccoli/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the tomatoes are beginning to soften, add your <strong>tomato paste </strong>and <strong>'Nduja</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) to the pan and cook for a further 1-2 min, breaking the<strong> '</strong>Nduja up in the pan as you go</p><p>Add your <strong>arborio rice</strong> and cook for 1 min, stirring to coat the grains in the sauce</p><p>Add the <strong>chicken stock</strong> a ladle at a time, stirring continuously for 25-30 min or until all of the stock is absorbed and the rice is cooked</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-nduja-risotto-with-zesty-tenderstem-broccoli/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the risotto is cooking, zest of<strong> half</strong> your <strong>lime[s] </strong>(try to grate lightly with a micro-plane or sharp box grater and avoid grating the white pith, as this is very bitter)</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-nduja-risotto-with-zesty-tenderstem-broccoli/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Chop your <strong>Tenderstem broccoli</strong> in half lengthways</p><p>When the risotto is almost ready, heat a separate large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped Tenderstem broccoli </strong>and cook for 10-12 min or until slightly charred and tender with a slight bite</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-nduja-risotto-with-zesty-tenderstem-broccoli/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the risotto is ready, stir through your <strong>soft cheese</strong>, <strong>half</strong> your <strong>grated</strong> <strong>Italian hard cheese</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) and a squeeze of <strong>lime juice </strong>(not sure about citrus? Try using less!)</p><p>Give everything a good mix up and cook for a further 1-2 min \u2013 this is your <strong>spicy</strong> <strong>'Nduja risotto</strong></p><p>Cut the <strong>remaining lime</strong> into 1 wedge per person</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-nduja-risotto-with-zesty-tenderstem-broccoli/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>spicy 'Nduja risotto </strong>in a bowl and top with the <strong>pan-fried Tenderstem</strong></p><p>Sprinkle the<strong> remaining grated Italian hard cheese</strong> and <strong>lime zest </strong>over the Tenderstem broccoli \u2013 this is<strong> your zesty Tenderstem broccoli</strong></p><p>Garnish with a <strong>lime wedge</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
